## 🚀 GitHub Integration

### Repository Structure for Cross-Project Documentation
```
research-exec/ (Main GitHub Repository)
├── CROSS_PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md  # This file - central navigation
├── README.md                             # Main project documentation
├── methodology/                          # Universal frameworks
├── src/templates/                        # PRD and task templates
└── workflow/                            # Cross-project workflows

External Projects (Referenced):
├── ../agent-orchestrator/               # Implementation project
└── ../mcp-servers-info/                 # Research repository
```

### GitHub Navigation Strategy
- **Central Index**: This file serves as the single source of truth for cross-project navigation
- **Local Links**: All research-exec links are relative and work on GitHub
- **External References**: Links to sibling projects use relative paths
- **Documentation Access**: GitHub renders this index with full link functionality

---

*This index provides comprehensive navigation between code implementations and their corresponding documentation across the entire research execution workspace. Since it's located in the research-exec project, it's accessible through GitHub and serves as the central navigation hub for all three projects.*
